  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nThe order of operations in setting up the checkpoint sync database leads to an attempt to finalize the checkpoint sync block before the `origin-checkpoint-block-root` key has been saved to the DB. This key is used as a special case when validating finalized blocks in `updateFinalizedBlockRoots`. Without the key, this routine scans to the checkpoint blocks parent and raises an error when the block corresponding to the parent_root can't be found. \r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nno this bug came in with the new feature\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\nrun:\r\n```\r\nbazel run //cmd/beacon-chain\r\n--weak-subjectivity-checkpoint=0x48e501971065de71d95bfc29f711e8889ac091c54b7626ba13b1eeaa0c392255:83520 \\\r\n--checkpoint-sync-url=http://localhost:3500 \\\r\n--prater \\\r\n--datadir=/var/lib/prysm/prater/checkpoint-sync \\\r\n--accept-terms-of-use \\\r\n--enable-debug-rpc-endpoints \\\r\n--grpc-max-msg-size=55568081 \\\r\n--http-web3provider=http://localhost:8545 \\\r\n--monitoring-port=8081 \\\r\n--p2p-tcp-port=13001 \\\r\n--p2p-udp-port=12001 \\\r\n--pprofport=6061 \\\r\n--grpc-gateway-port=3501 \\\r\n--rpc-port=4001 \\\r\n--genesis-state /var/lib/prysm/prater/genesis.ssz\r\n```\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n```\r\ntime=\"2022-03-30 13:31:06\" level=info msg=\"calling SaveState w/ blockRoot=48e501971065de71d95bfc29f711e8889ac091c54b7626ba13b1eeaa0c392255\" prefix=db\r\ntime=\"2022-03-30 13:31:06\" level=error msg=\"could not mark checkpoint sync block as finalized: signed beacon block can't be nil\" prefix=main\r\n```\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\n\r\nn/a\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\npre-release\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\n\r\n",
